parameters: Chieftain: "Ah, you've arrived."
Kru: "Chieftain! What on earth is this..."

Umi: "Chieftain... Mia is... and the villagers too... What should Umi
do..."

Chieftain: "Hmm... It's said to be an epidemic that occurs once every few
decades in this region. This is my first encounter with it, but I have
heard from my predecessor how to deal with it."
Kru: "Then it can be cured, right?!"

Chieftain: "I can't assure you, but it's not like there's nothing we can
do. It is said that a medicine made from a herb called Makiro grass, which
grows on Mount Tamagawa, is effective against the disease."
Kru: "Then we just need to get that grass!"

Chieftain: "That's right... However, the Makiro grass only grows at the
summit of Mount Tamagawa. The mountain is quite high, and the demons
nesting there are very strong."
Kru: "I'll go! I'll leave right away."

Chieftain: "Thank you. However, even for you, fighting the demons living on
Mount Tamagawa and reaching the summit will be a heavy burden... Therefore,
Umi..."
Umi: "Eh...?"
Chieftain: "Would you accompany Kru to the mountain?"

Kru: "Umi... I know you're worried about Mia, but if we go quickly and
make the medicine, she'll surely get better!"
Umi: "...no... I can't..."

Chieftain: "Umi, I understand that I'm asking you to do something
difficult. But right now, the only ones who can move in this village are
you and Kru..."
Umi: "Umi... is scared..."
Kru: "Umi!"
Chieftain: "It seems impossible after all..."
Kru: "Chieftain! Is there a reason for this?"
Chieftain: "Hmm, then let me tell you as well..."
particle set diamonddust_w weather
particle set diamonddust_w2 weather
particle set light_leak_s screen def spriteset
Kru: "What! Chieftain... what is this⁉"

Chieftain: "This is called a 'Seed of Memory.' It's tied to strong memories
and has the power to awaken them."
Kru: "Why do you have that..."

Chieftain: "Hmm... I want you to properly understand about Umi. With the
power of this Seed of Memory, I will show you our memories."

Chieftain: "Umi has never left this forest... You know that her parents are
deceased, right?"
Kru: "Yes, I'm aware."

Chieftain: "Her mother fell ill and passed away shortly after giving birth
to Umi... She had a frail body..."
particle set diamonddust_w weather
particle set diamonddust_w2 weather
particle set light_leak_s screen def spriteset

Chieftain: "By the time the villagers arrived, Umi's father had already
passed away... and with that shock, Umi's mother also passed away soon
after..."

Chieftain: "Umi blamed herself terribly. She regretted leaving the forest
on her own accord and became unable to speak for about three years..."
Kru: "Such a thing happened..."

Chieftain: "Since then, Umi has been unable to leave this forest... I
wanted to do something to help her, but there was nothing I could do..."

Kru: "(I see... So that's why she said she couldn't go to see the sea that
time...)"
Chieftain: "That's where you come in... Could you guide Umi?"
Kru: "Eh? Me?"

Chieftain: "Yes, you... I've known Umi since she was a child. That Umi, who
doesn't open her heart to others, truly smiles when she's with you."

Chieftain: "I'm sure you can lead Umi in a good direction... I'm counting
on you."
Kru: "...I don't know if I can do it, but... I'll try!!"
showHpGauge
"Going to see Umi"
Chieftain: "I'm counting on you."
Chieftain: "I'm glad you made it back safely. So, the herbs!?"
Kru: "Yes! Here they are."
Chieftain: "This is indeed... Both of you... thank you... thank you."
Umi: "I'm so relieved... With this, everyone will be saved."
Chieftain: "That's right. Now, let's hurry and process it!"

We hurriedly prepared the medicine with the chieftain... Thanks to the
preparations made by the villagers who were safe, we were able to get the
medicine quickly...

During the process, Umi, perhaps unable to hide her anxiety, tightly
grasped my hand. I firmly grasped back, feeling a strong desire to protect
her.
And once the medicine was ready, we immediately went to give it to Mia.
Chieftain: "Ah, you've arrived. I have an important request for you."
Kru: "Yes. What would you like to discuss?"

Chieftain: "Well, everyone will be gathering shortly, so we'll talk then.
Just wait a little."
Chieftain: "I need to speak with Umi. Can you bring her here?"

Chieftain: "You've arrived. Umi, that look on your face... Have you made up
your mind?"
Umi: "Chieftain. You're asking too much of Umi."

Chieftain: "Umi-chan! It can't be helped! This is all for your sake, Umi-
chan."

Umi: "You're joking. Thank you for everything up to now, Chieftain. Umi
will be fine."
Kru: "Umi..."
Chieftain: "Umi... To think the once timid Umi has grown so much."
Umi: "Chieftain. I'm going."
Kru: "Chieftain. I'll do my best to ensure we get a good response."
Chieftain: "Both of you... I'm counting on you."
Chieftain: "I'm counting on you."

Chieftain: "Kru... Your efforts this time were truly commendable. You did
well to repel that great army and return. And as one of the villagers, I
say this: thank you for saving our village. I thought it was all over... I
thought we were done for..."

Kru: "Indeed... I also thought it might be impossible, but thanks to Umi,
we somehow managed to pull through."

Umi: "That's not true. Umi didn't do anything. It was Kru who worked so
hard... until he was all battered and bruised."

Chieftain: "Kru, and Umi... I can't thank you enough. But having overcome
this crisis, I no longer worry about the future of our village. Kru, Umi...
I entrust the rest to you. Please take care of our village."
Kru: "Huh? What do you mean by that...?"
Umi: "Chieftain?"

Chieftain: "I have decided to retire. Kru, I want you to become the new
chieftain of our village!"
Kru: "What⁉ Me⁉"
Chieftain: "Yes, you! There's no one else but you!"

Umi: "Chieftain... please try a little harder. Kru and Umi are going to get
married and relax for a while."
Chieftain: "What! What's this all about! When did this happen!"
Kru: "Well, I proposed before the final battle..."

Umi: "Chieftain... sorry for the late report. Umi has decided to get
married."
Chieftain: "What a thing to say... what a thing."
Kru: "Ch-Chieftain?"

Chieftain: "I am... happy... to see such a day... Umi, who was once so
injured she couldn't speak... is finally getting married...
congratulations... congratulations to you both!"
Kru: "Chieftain, thank you very much."
Umi: "Chieftain, Umi will be happy. Thank you for everything up until now."

Chieftain: "Ah, be happy. But I insist on Kru becoming the chieftain! It
doesn't have to be right away! There are various procedures to go through
anyway."
Kru: "Procedures?"

Chieftain: "Yes. Well, we'll discuss that in due course. The villagers also
wish for you to become the chieftain. Will you accept?"
Umi: "Kru... everyone in the village will feel safe with Kru as chieftain."
Kru: "Well... if I'm good enough, I'll accept."

Chieftain: "Is that so! Thank you! What a joyous day this is! Now, first
things first, we must hold a wedding ceremony! Let there be a feast, a
feast!"
